description.narrative: An estimated 29,633 children and adults;have access to safe and accessible channels to report sexual exploitation and abuse. However, the Violence Against Children Survey (VACS) confirms that many, if not most, children cannot recognise all forms of sexual violence as such. Increasing understanding, reporting and help-seeking behaviour have thus become key priorities for UNICEF’s future child protection C4D interventions. The promising results so far from the UPSHIFT pilot and support to young people living with HIV to increase adolescent’s agency in social development, and the integrated teen club service delivery model with gardening, are also ready for further scale-up. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/12/2021
